formalText: Found it hard for him to be specific about what he experienced.
Told him it would helpful if he showed what it means to have dark feelings and what he associate to it bringing things up memories.
He replied "I'm still working on this shit and it's you know, hard".
Comes in saying, "so yeah I have a lot going on
definitely like a situational depression thing maybe a little bit
just
been a little bit of a roller coaster last several days and even within the same day
He says everyday he doesn't know what is going on,
He feels really dark and depressed and realizes he is  in those moments more than before.
He feels like "wow, I must hate myself so much"
He says, "Like that's even happening right now.
I'm handling things so well, but I have trouble."
He has very dark feelings about himself
He is trying to date on match.com but it isn't working well
He hadn't connected that when he talks to women online, he gets really anxious.
He finds dating online depressing.
Directly states, "I'm depressed.
I'm fucking anxious"
He has moments where he feel really lonely and frustrated.
And then it becomes a vicious cycle.
Every person has a different experience of online dating, and he focused on the generalizations of it and finds it difficult to find his own experience.
He said he suddenly got really get anxious and said "I'm not down involve my fucking problems and I can't suck it up and be tough.
With girls, he feels like he is not articulate and then he talks on and on which makes it worse.
He wants to talk about real problems with a girl in a relationship,  not just complaining and complaining about some asshole at work.
Said, "each girl could be a chapter and I have a very long book"

not going to work.
